article.description: Andrea Riley had 22 points and 10 assists, and Oklahoma State (No. 23 ESPN/USA Today, No. 22 AP) beat UNLV 88-73 on Saturday.
article.headline: Riley has 22 points, 10 assists as Oklahoma State rolls
article.story:
LAS VEGAS -- Andrea Riley had 22 points and 10 assists, and Oklahoma State (No. 23 ESPN/USA Today, No. 22 AP) beat UNLV 88-73 on Saturday.

The Cowgirls (7-7) took a 55-52 lead on Taylor Hardeman's 3-pointer with just under 16 minutes left, then completed a 12-0 run that gave them a 64-52 advantage with 12:39 remaining. Shaunte Smith made two consecutive lay-ups during the key run for Oklahoma State.

Hardeman had 16 points for Oklahoma State (7-2) on 5-for-6 shooting. Shyvon Spears added 13 points and 13 rebounds.

Freshman Jamie Smith led the Lady Rebels (5-5) with 27 points. India Chaney added 14.
